       (28724,'Crafter''s Delineation','A detailed outline of complex crafting techniques. One delineation is consumed when using a specialist action.',26188,999,1,60,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28765,'Skybuilders'' Yew Log','The distinct lack of trees is one of many problems the first people to settle in Ishgard chose to ignore, making this otherwise commonplace material─sourced from the East Shroud─extremely valuable.',22409,999,20,49,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28857,'Replica Sky Rat Ironclad Boots of Striking',NULL,47073,1,1,37,1,TRUE,TRUE,FALSE,TRUE,TRUE),
       (28766,'Skybuilders'' Iron Ore','While this may look much like any other iron ore found in middle La Noscea, there are subtle differences that only an expert in the field will recognize. The name, for one, is considerably longer.',21202,999,20,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28767,'Skybuilders'' Fine Sand','This sand gathered in central Thanalan is not only fine, but extremely well behaved, choosing to stay in one closely knit lump while jostling alongside the rest of your possessions.',21464,999,20,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28768,'Skybuilders'' Hemp','Though this hardy plant can grow almost anywhere, the snow-blasted precipices of Ishgard have so far proven too steep a challenge for it to overcome. This particular specimen was harvested in lower La Noscea, an environment far more conducive to plant life─or any sort of life, for that matter.',21654,999,20,50,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28769,'Skybuilders'' Ash Log','Ash! A-Ah! Savior of the Firmament!♪',22407,999,40,49,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28770,'Skybuilders'' Rock Salt','Although upper La Noscea seems rather a distant location from which to source something as simple as salt, the Ishgardians are nothing if not particular in their tastes.',22617,999,40,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28771,'Skybuilders'' Electrum Ore','The electrum ore found in upper La Noscea is believed to be far better suited to the skybuilders'' needs than any other variety. Were anyone to ask them why, they would, in most cases be met with a response along the line of, “Because it just is.”',21217,999,40,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28772,'Skybuilders'' Iron Sand','The tradition of measuring powdered substances in units of “pinches” has been the cause of many arguments, largely due to differences in finger size between the various races. Folk in eastern Thanalan, where this sample was gathered, have been known to ask Lalafells to measure when selling, and Roegadyn when buying, for obvious reasons.',21204,999,40,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28773,'Skybuilders'' Flax','It is a well known fact among botanists that the flax in the South Shroud is superior to every other kind, for reasons far too complicated and boring for anyone else to care about.',21651,999,40,50,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28774,'Skybuilders'' Spring Water','Having only traveled the relatively short distance from the Coerthas central highlands to Ishgard, this spring water is still remarkably fresh, though the icy chill threatens to freeze it inside the bottle.',22614,999,40,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28775,'Skybuilders'' Camphorwood Log','Few members of the mortal races are equipped to make the perilous journey to the Churning Mists, and those who do normally hope to have more than a log or two to show for their troubles.',22405,999,150,49,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28776,'Skybuilders'' Straw','Why the skybuilders would specify that their straw be brought from the Dravanian forelands is anyone''s guess. Perhaps the smell helps their chocobos sleep more peacefully?',21653,999,150,50,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28777,'Skybuilders'' Hardsilver Ore','The time spent mining this ore in the Dravanian hinterlands would perhaps have seemed less arduous if you had the faintest idea how the skybuilders plan to use it.',21223,999,150,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28778,'Skybuilders'' Mythrite Sand','You have a sneaking suspicion that you may have lost some of the sand during the return journey from the Sea of Clouds, though the amount you have in your possession should still suffice.',21218,999,150,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28779,'Skybuilders'' Tea Leaves','The thought of happy skybuilders drinking delicious tea was the only motivation you needed as you risked life and limb gathering these leaves in the Sea of Clouds.',25020,999,150,44,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28780,'Skybuilders'' Dravanian Spring Water','There are easier places to collect spring water than the Dravanian forelands, though it seems your personal safety is not especially high on the skybuilders'' list of concerns.',22614,999,150,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28781,'Skybuilders'' Urunday Log','Compared to most places in Gyr Abania, the Peaks has more than its fair share of trees, so who would object to you taking a few logs? Bloodthirsty Qiqirn and rampaging ruud suuds, that''s who. Or perhaps they just see you as an easy meal?',22420,999,290,49,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28782,'Skybuilders'' Nightsteel Ore','The Ruby Sea is not especially well known as a prime location for mining, though those who are nautically minded can uncover all sorts of rare and unique treasures. Whether the skybuilders choose to turn this into fine jewelry or something more mundane, like a tea strainer, remains to be seen.',21203,999,290,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28783,'Skybuilders'' Adder','Venomous snakes are something of a rarity in Ishgard, so the skybuilders have ordered that some be delivered from the Azim Steppe to help improve morale. Workers displaying a lack of enthusiasm will be given some time in “the pit” to rediscover their commitment to the cause.',22620,999,290,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28784,'Skybuilders'' Molybdenum Ore','While the Lochs are better known as a source of salt, the rich veins of ore are drawing in miners from far and wide.',21227,999,290,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28785,'Skybuilders'' Horsetail','Yanxia is rich in both flora and fauna, and horsetail forms a major part of the diet of many grazing creatures.',26592,999,290,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28786,'Skybuilders'' Ala Mhigan Rock Salt','When an Ishgardian culinarian stated that her latest dish needed a pinch of salt, the skybuilders sought out the very best, though perhaps more than a single pinch would be required to make the lengthy journey to the Lochs worthwhile.',22617,999,290,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28787,'Skybuilders'' Ruby Sea Water','While water from the Ruby Sea may not sound particularly appealing, this was actually brought from a small freshwater spring on one of the surrounding islands. Drinking this is unlikely to result in life-threatening dehydration.',22678,999,290,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28788,'Skybuilders'' Durium Sand','A pinch of anything tends not to be an awful lot, though this particular sand from the Azim Steppe is apparently worth more than its weight in gold.',21218,999,290,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28789,'Skybuilders'' Vine','Quite why a particular type of vine that can only be found in the Azim Steppe is necessary to the skybuilders'' plans has yet to be explained. Perhaps they are planning to surprise you with a work of surpassing genius? Or perhaps not.',21672,999,290,50,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28790,'Skybuilders'' White Ash Log','Obviously, none of the skybuilders has even heard of the Rak''tika Greatwood, though the specific qualities they seek in their timber can most easily be found in the white ash trees that grow there.',22406,999,430,49,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28791,'Skybuilders'' Reef Rock','If a porous rock from the bottom of the ocean is required in the rebuilding of Ishgard, then so be it. Your job is to mine, not question the reasoning behind such dubious demands.',21203,999,430,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28792,'Skybuilders'' Truegold Ore','Why submit a boring chunk of gold ore when you can bring one all the way from Il Mheg instead?',21212,999,430,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28858,'Replica Sky Rat Mask of Aiming',NULL,40497,1,1,31,1,TRUE,TRUE,FALSE,TRUE,TRUE),
       (28859,'Replica Sky Rat Harness of Aiming',NULL,43320,1,1,33,1,TRUE,TRUE,FALSE,TRUE,TRUE),
       (28793,'Skybuilders'' Cotton Boll','This cotton must be very special indeed for you to bring it all the way from Lakeland in the First. You can only hope that the skybuilders appreciate you going the extra malm. And traveling to another world.',25032,999,430,50,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28794,'Skybuilders'' Dawn Lizard','One day, this poor lizard is chasing other, smaller scurrying creatures across the desert plains of Amh Araeng, and the next, it is being transported to another world and dragged lashing and kicking to Ishgard. The chances of the cold-blooded scalekin being content in its frozen new surroundings are slim at best, and you can only hope that the skybuilders are grateful to you for supplying a miserable and motionless lizard.',22684,999,430,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28795,'Skybuilders'' Wheat','Were the other contributors to hear that you traveled to Amh Araeng in the First simply to procure wheat, they would think you are just trying to show off.',21653,999,430,44,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28796,'Skybuilders'' Truegold Sand','The isle of Kholusia is known by the inhabitants of Norvrandt to have the very finest of gold sand. Whether this is up to the impossibly high standards of the skybuilders will only become apparent when it is submitted for inspection.',21214,999,430,47,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28797,'Skybuilders'' Highland Spring Water','Any water gathered from Il Mheg is likely to have been enchanted by either the pixies or the Fuath, though that is a problem for the skybuilders, not you, to worry about.',22678,999,430,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
       (28798,'Skybuilders'' Resin','Thankfully, the resin appears to have suffered no ill effects during your return from the Rak''tika Greatwood, meaning that it is still a gelatinous blob with seemingly no practical application whatsoever.',22638,999,430,53,NULL,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE,FALSE),
